                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440610-name-1403" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440610-name-1403" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440610-name-1403" type="surname" value="LANGLEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440610-name-1403" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>ROBERT LANGLEY</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a labourer, and live in Garrett-lane, Wandsworth. I was at supper between twelve and one in the night of the 28th of May—I went out backwards for two or three minutes, and when I came back I missed my handkerchief—the prisoner had come in and asked for lodgings—I asked him if he had got the handkerchief—he said, "No," and he pulled out two, which were not mine—he was searched, and my handkerchief found in his pocket—this is it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> I went to ask for a lodging, and found the handkerchief three or four yards from the door. <hi rend="italic">Witness.</hi> No such thing.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> He asked if I had found a handkerchief; I said, no, not that; I knew of that belonged to him; I asked if I could have a lodging; he said, no, it was no lodging-house; I went down the lane, and he followed and took me; I picked the handkerchief up.</p>
